<subSubSection id="F4C86558BD5CFF929EDFFAC3DAC1DD6A" pageId="9" pageNumber="536" type="key">
<keyStep id="07262E76BD5CFF929EDFFAC3DAC1DF97" pageId="9" pageNumber="536">
<paragraph id="BC6D36D3BD5CFF929EDFFAC3DAC1DF5C" blockId="9.[151,1437,1350,1871]" pageId="9" pageNumber="536">
<keyLead id="072395E6BD5CFF929EDFFAC3DAC1DF5C" pageId="9" pageNumber="536">
1. Clypeus strongly convex, distinctly projecting forward in lateral view; clypeus granulose-mat, distinctly differentiated from irregularly rugose face; hind trochanter, trochantellus and femur black............... 
<taxonomicName id="7BD24D50BD5CFF929A75FAE6DAC1DF5C" authority="Uchida &amp; Momoi, 1960" authorityName="Uchida &amp; Momoi" authorityYear="1960" box="[1085,1436,1379,1401]" class="Insecta" family="Ichneumonidae" genus="Scenocharops" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="9" pageNumber="536" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="koreana">
<emphasis id="8EA6EAC1BD5CFF929A75FAE6DAC1DF5C" bold="true" box="[1085,1436,1379,1401]" pageId="9" pageNumber="536">
<emphasis id="8EA6EAC1BD5CFF929A75FAE6DBFADF5D" bold="true" box="[1085,1191,1379,1401]" italics="true" pageId="9" pageNumber="536">S. koreana</emphasis>
<bibRefCitation id="D8434B22BD5CFF929AE6FAE6DAC1DF5C" author="Uchida, T. &amp; Momoi, S." box="[1198,1436,1379,1401]" pageId="9" pageNumber="536" pagination="11 - 13" refId="ref10239" refString="Uchida, T. &amp; Momoi, S. (1960) Description of a new species of the genus Scenocharops Uchida from Korea (Hymenoptera, Ichneumonidae). Insecta Matsumurana, 23, 11 - 13." type="journal article" year="1960">Uchida &amp; Momoi, 1960</bibRefCitation>
</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
</keyLead>
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="BC6D36D3BD5CFF929EDFFA04DAC1DF97" blockId="9.[151,1437,1350,1871]" pageId="9" pageNumber="536">
<keyLead id="072395E6BD5CFF929EDFFA04DAC1DF97" pageId="9" pageNumber="536">-. Clypeus flat, in same plane as face in lateral view; sculpture of clypeus similar to face, rugose; hind trochanter, trochantellus and femur usually yellowish brown....................................................................... 2</keyLead>
</paragraph>
</keyStep>
<keyStep id="07262E76BD5CFF929EDFFA39DAC1DFCB" pageId="9" pageNumber="536">
<paragraph id="BC6D36D3BD5CFF929EDFFA39DAC1DFF5" blockId="9.[151,1437,1350,1871]" box="[151,1436,1468,1490]" pageId="9" pageNumber="536">
<keyLead id="072395E6BD5CFF929EDFFA39DAC1DFF5" box="[151,1436,1468,1490]" pageId="9" pageNumber="536">2. Fore wing areolet present............................................................................... 3</keyLead>
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="BC6D36D3BD5CFF929EDFFA5CDAC1DFCB" blockId="9.[151,1437,1350,1871]" box="[151,1436,1497,1519]" pageId="9" pageNumber="536">
<keyLead id="072395E6BD5CFF929EDFFA5CDAC1DFCB" box="[151,1436,1497,1519]" pageId="9" pageNumber="536">-. Fore wing areolet absent................................................................................ 5</keyLead>
</paragraph>
</keyStep>
<keyStep id="07262E76BD5CFF929EDFFA73DAC1DC47" pageId="9" pageNumber="536">
<paragraph id="BC6D36D3BD5CFF929EDFFA73DAC0DC0D" blockId="9.[151,1437,1350,1871]" pageId="9" pageNumber="536">
<keyLead id="072395E6BD5CFF929EDFFA73DAC0DC0D" pageId="9" pageNumber="536">
3. Mesopleuron shiny and sparsely punctate medially; scape and pedicel blackish; hind trochanter, trochantellus, and basal half of hind femur blackish brown....................................................... 
<taxonomicName id="7BD24D50BD5CFF929A30F996DAC0DC0D" authority="(Sonan, 1929)" baseAuthorityName="Sonan" baseAuthorityYear="1929" box="[1144,1437,1555,1577]" class="Insecta" family="Ichneumonidae" genus="Scenocharops" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="9" pageNumber="536" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="flavipetiolus">
<emphasis id="8EA6EAC1BD5CFF929A30F996DAC0DC0D" bold="true" box="[1144,1437,1555,1577]" pageId="9" pageNumber="536">
<emphasis id="8EA6EAC1BD5CFF929A30F996DA57DC0D" bold="true" box="[1144,1290,1555,1577]" italics="true" pageId="9" pageNumber="536">S. flavipetiolus</emphasis>
(
<bibRefCitation id="D8434B22BD5CFF929B5FF996DAC8DC0D" author="Sonan, J." box="[1303,1429,1555,1577]" pageId="9" pageNumber="536" pagination="415 - 425" refId="ref10031" refString="Sonan, J. (1929) A few host-known Ichneumonidae found in Formosa (Hym.). Transactions of the Natural History Society of Formosa, 19 (104), 415 - 425." type="journal article" year="1929">Sonan, 1929</bibRefCitation>
)
</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
</keyLead>
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="BC6D36D3BD5CFF929EDFF9B4DAC1DC47" blockId="9.[151,1437,1350,1871]" pageId="9" pageNumber="536">
<keyLead id="072395E6BD5CFF929EDFF9B4DAC1DC47" pageId="9" pageNumber="536">-. Mesopleuron dull and rugose-punctate or rugose-reticulate medially; scape and pedicel yellowish brown; hind trochanter, trochantellus, and femur yellowish brown.................................................................. 4</keyLead>
</paragraph>
</keyStep>
<keyStep id="07262E76BD5CFF929EDFF9E9DAC1DCFC" pageId="9" pageNumber="536">
<paragraph id="BC6D36D3BD5CFF929EDFF9E9DAC1DCBA" blockId="9.[151,1437,1350,1871]" pageId="9" pageNumber="536">
<keyLead id="072395E6BD5CFF929EDFF9E9DAC1DCBA" pageId="9" pageNumber="536">
4. Malar space 0.35–0.40× basal width of mandible; mesopleuron rugose-punctate; hind tarsal claw with 9 teeth................................................................................................. 
<taxonomicName id="7BD24D50BD5CFF929A9EF90CDAC1DCBA" authority="He, 1980" authorityName="He" authorityYear="1980" box="[1238,1436,1673,1694]" class="Insecta" family="Ichneumonidae" genus="Scenocharps" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="9" pageNumber="536" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="parasae">
<emphasis id="8EA6EAC1BD5CFF929A9EF90CDAC1DCBA" bold="true" box="[1238,1436,1673,1694]" pageId="9" pageNumber="536">
<emphasis id="8EA6EAC1BD5CFF929A9EF90CDA60DCBA" bold="true" box="[1238,1341,1673,1694]" italics="true" pageId="9" pageNumber="536">S. parasae</emphasis>
<bibRefCitation id="D8434B22BD5CFF929B0BF90CDAC1DCBA" author="He, J. H." box="[1347,1436,1673,1694]" pageId="9" pageNumber="536" pagination="79 - 83" refId="ref9456" refString="He, J. H. (1980) Two new species and a new record of the genus Scenocharops Uchida from China (Hymenoptera: Ichneumonidae). Journal of Zhejiang Agricultural University, 6 (2), 79 - 83. [in Chinese with English summary]" type="journal article" year="1980">He, 1980</bibRefCitation>
</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
</keyLead>
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="BC6D36D3BD5CFF929EDFF922DAC1DCFC" blockId="9.[151,1437,1350,1871]" pageId="9" pageNumber="536">
<keyLead id="072395E6BD5CFF929EDFF922DAC1DCFC" pageId="9" pageNumber="536">
-. Malar space ca 0.47× basal width of mandible; mesopleuron rugose-reticulate; hind tarsal claw with 3–5 teeth............................................................................. 
<taxonomicName id="7BD24D50BD5CFF929DB1F946DAC1DCFC" authority="Gupta &amp; Maheshwary, 1971" authorityName="Gupta &amp; Maheshwary" authorityYear="1971" box="[1017,1436,1731,1753]" class="Insecta" family="Ichneumonidae" genus="Scenocharps" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="9" pageNumber="536" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="montanus">
<emphasis id="8EA6EAC1BD5CFF929DB1F946DAC1DCFC" bold="true" box="[1017,1436,1731,1753]" pageId="9" pageNumber="536">
<emphasis id="8EA6EAC1BD5CFF929DB1F946DB28DCFD" bold="true" box="[1017,1141,1731,1753]" italics="true" pageId="9" pageNumber="536">S. montanus</emphasis>
<bibRefCitation id="D8434B22BD5CFF929A33F946DAC1DCFC" author="Gupta, V. K. &amp; Maheshwary, S." box="[1147,1436,1731,1753]" pageId="9" pageNumber="536" pagination="453 - 480" refId="ref9369" refString="Gupta, V. K. &amp; Maheshwary, S. (1971) Indian species of Charops Holmgren (Hymenoptera: Ichneumonidae). Oriental Insects, 4, 453 - 480. https: // doi. org / 10.1080 / 00305316.1970.10433983" type="journal article" year="1971">Gupta &amp; Maheshwary, 1971</bibRefCitation>
</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
</keyLead>
</paragraph>
</keyStep>
<keyStep id="07262E76BD5CFF929EDFF964DAC1DD6A" pageId="9" pageNumber="536">
<paragraph id="BC6D36D3BD5CFF929EDFF964DAC1DD37" blockId="9.[151,1437,1350,1871]" pageId="9" pageNumber="536">
<keyLead id="072395E6BD5CFF929EDFF964DAC1DD37" pageId="9" pageNumber="536">
5. Mesopleuron punctate medially (
<figureCitation id="24E92A56BD5CFF929C69F964DD33DCD3" box="[545,622,1761,1783]" captionStart="FIGURE 6" captionStartId="12.[151,250,1928,1952]" captionTargetBox="[204,1384,181,1905]" captionTargetId="figure-37@12.[204,1384,181,1905]" captionTargetPageId="12" captionText="FIGURE 6. Scenocharops yunnanensis sp. nov., holotype, female. A, fore wing; B, hind wing; C, mesopleuron and metapleuron; D, propodeum; E, ovipositor; F, head, anterior view; G, head, dorsal view; H, mesoscutum; I, first metasomal segment; J, cocoon; K, hind tarsal claw." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6531148" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6531148/files/figure.png" pageId="9" pageNumber="536">Fig. 6C</figureCitation>
); hind tarsal claw distinctly upcurved apically (
<figureCitation id="24E92A56BD5CFF929A72F964DBD4DCD3" box="[1082,1161,1761,1783]" captionStart="FIGURE 6" captionStartId="12.[151,250,1928,1952]" captionTargetBox="[204,1384,181,1905]" captionTargetId="figure-37@12.[204,1384,181,1905]" captionTargetPageId="12" captionText="FIGURE 6. Scenocharops yunnanensis sp. nov., holotype, female. A, fore wing; B, hind wing; C, mesopleuron and metapleuron; D, propodeum; E, ovipositor; F, head, anterior view; G, head, dorsal view; H, mesoscutum; I, first metasomal segment; J, cocoon; K, hind tarsal claw." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6531148" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6531148/files/figure.png" pageId="9" pageNumber="536">Fig. 6K</figureCitation>
); scape and pedicel blackish brown (
<figureCitation id="24E92A56BD5CFF929F64F97BDE2BDD30" box="[300,374,1790,1812]" captionStart="FIGURE 6" captionStartId="12.[151,250,1928,1952]" captionTargetBox="[204,1384,181,1905]" captionTargetId="figure-37@12.[204,1384,181,1905]" captionTargetPageId="12" captionText="FIGURE 6. Scenocharops yunnanensis sp. nov., holotype, female. A, fore wing; B, hind wing; C, mesopleuron and metapleuron; D, propodeum; E, ovipositor; F, head, anterior view; G, head, dorsal view; H, mesoscutum; I, first metasomal segment; J, cocoon; K, hind tarsal claw." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6531148" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6531148/files/figure.png" pageId="9" pageNumber="536">Fig. 6F</figureCitation>
); hind femur blackish brown (
<figureCitation id="24E92A56BD5CFF929CD0F97BDD8DDD30" box="[664,720,1790,1812]" captionStart="FIGURE 5" captionStartId="11.[151,250,2009,2033]" captionTargetBox="[164,1424,1033,1986]" captionTargetId="figure-234@11.[164,1424,1033,1986]" captionTargetPageId="11" captionText="FIGURE 5. Scenocharops yunnanensis sp. nov., holotype, female, habitus." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6531146" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6531146/files/figure.png" pageId="9" pageNumber="536">Fig. 5</figureCitation>
)....................................... 
<emphasis id="8EA6EAC1BD5CFF929AFBF97BDAC1DD37" bold="true" box="[1203,1436,1790,1811]" pageId="9" pageNumber="536">
<taxonomicName id="7BD24D50BD5CFF929AFBF97BDA14DD37" authority="Han &amp; Achterberg &amp; Chen, 2022" authorityName="Han &amp; Achterberg &amp; Chen" authorityYear="2022" box="[1203,1353,1790,1811]" class="Insecta" family="Ichneumonidae" genus="Scenocharops" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="9" pageNumber="536" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="yunnanensis" status="sp. nov.">
<emphasis id="8EA6EAC1BD5CFF929AFBF97BDA14DD37" bold="true" box="[1203,1353,1790,1811]" italics="true" pageId="9" pageNumber="536">S. yunnanensis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<taxonomicNameLabel id="959557BABD5CFF929B18F97BDAC1DD37" box="[1360,1436,1790,1811]" pageId="9" pageNumber="536" rank="species">sp. nov.</taxonomicNameLabel>
</emphasis>
</keyLead>
